§I CSSL-SYNTAX-CONSERVATISM (patterns established this wave)
  ⟦
    USE                         : free-fn surface (¬ method-receivers) · tuple-variants (¬ struct-variants) · single-expression match-arms (¬ block-arms)
                                  StrSlice (¬ &str fat-pointer) · Vec<T> (heap-backed) · Option<T> by-value (¬ Option<&T>)
                                  effect-row as doc-comment (¬ in-fn-sig) · cap as i32/i64-packed (¬ Cap<X> generic)
                                  matches stdlib/fs.cssl + stdlib/net.cssl + stdlib/option.cssl + stdlib/result.cssl precedent
    AVOID                       : @vertex/@fragment + refinement-types + effect-rows-in-fn-sig until parser-slice lands
                                  block-body match-arms · struct-variants · &mut self · ?-operator
    MIGRATION-MECHANICAL        : every // N! flagged divergence collapses to spec-canonical form once parser slice lands
  ⟧

